.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED133688FFC6FFF61FC38589862201F2" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4">Tergites 1 and 2 dark yellow pilose; tergite 3 dark yellow pilose with fascia of golden pile along posterior margin; tergites 4 and 5 dark yellow pilose on anterior half, black pilose on posterior half, with medially interrupted fascia of golden pile in between. Sternites yellow; long yellow pilose, sternite 1 with only two long thin setae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5B66503FFC6FFF61F93841A81CE003A" pageId="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="ED133688FFC6FFF61F93841A81CE003A" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61F93841A82720018" bold="true" box="[199,334,260,285]" pageId="4">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61D6C841B81660019" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2017" box="[568,602,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rex">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61D6C841B81660019" box="[568,602,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4">rex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(‘king’, in Latin) was chosen to emphasize the large size of this species in comparison with the other known species of 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61DD8843981D70045" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1852" box="[652,747,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61DD8843981D70045" box="[652,747,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4">Ubristes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5B66503FFC6FFF61F93845282C2031D" pageId="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="ED133688FFC6FFF61F93845282C2031D" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61F93845282020060" bold="true" box="[199,318,332,357]" pageId="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The only known specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61DD88452802D0061" authority="Reemer, 2017" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2017" box="[652,785,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rex" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61DD88452802D0061" box="[652,785,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="4">Ubristes rex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C4EB57E1FFC6FFF61C4C845280640060" box="[792,856,332,357]" pageId="4" rank="species">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61C4C845280640060" bold="true" box="[792,856,332,357]" pageId="4">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is considerably larger than the other known 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61A14845286A00060" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1852" box="[1344,1436,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61A14845286A00060" box="[1344,1436,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="4">Ubristes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species: 
<quantity id="2A549B6DFFC6FFF61FAC847182630082" box="[248,351,367,392]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="14.5">14.5 mm</quantity>
instead of 
<quantity id="2A549B6DFFC6FFF61EB2846E81690082" box="[486,597,368,392]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="8.0">8–11 mm</quantity>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61C40846F80A0008D" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1852" box="[788,924,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavitibia">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61C40846F80A0008D" box="[788,924,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4">U. flavitibia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its yellowish colouration (blackish in 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61AD5846F83C500A8" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavitibia">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61AD5846F83C500A8" italics="true" pageId="4">U. flavitibia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61E05848B814000A9" authority="Reemer, 2013 a" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" box="[337,636,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ictericus">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61E05848B82EC00A9" box="[337,464,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="4">U. ictericus</emphasis>
Reemer, 2013a
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the entirely yellow pilose hind legs (partly black pilose in 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61AD5848B83C800D5" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ictericus">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61AD5848B83C800D5" italics="true" pageId="4">U. ictericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the presence of golden pilose fasciae on tergites 3–5. From 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61CE684A787CE00D5" authority="Reemer, 2013 a" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" box="[946,1266,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaguarinus">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61CE684A7877400D5" box="[946,1096,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="4">U. jaguarinus</emphasis>
Reemer, 2013a
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the absence of dark brown maculae on the tergites. Furthermore, the face is produced more strongly ventrad in 
<taxonomicName id="2AAC4D0BFFC6FFF61A6484C3864F00F1" authority="Reemer, 2017" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2017" box="[1328,1395,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ubristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rex" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61A6484C3864F00F1" box="[1328,1395,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="4">U. rex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C4EB57E1FFC6FFF61A2E84C28392031D" pageId="4" rank="species">
<emphasis id="DFD8EA9AFFC6FFF61A2E84C28392031D" bold="true" pageId="4">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
than in the other three species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
